node.text:
I haven’t posted a YouTube video since college😅

Comment below anything you guys might want to see on my channel 🙏

The lil’ video editing work I did for insomniac recently brought back memories and reminded me just how much I love filming and editing (it just takes up a HELLA lot of time) and I’ve always wanted to vlog my raves, shoutout to @snewj, but knowing how crazy I get and how irresponsible I get with my belongings (learned my lesson after losing my phone and car keys at a festival) I didn’t trust myself carrying around my vlogging camera, much more having the attention span to vlog in the chaos of a rave. Soooo I just took hella ig stories instead and logged them on my highlights

It’s all good tho, since I love sharing the raw, real cringe af me with you guys... so I’m starting off my comeback with a new series named “the Uncensored Rave Vlogs” where I cleanup my highlights and move all my uncensored IG stories of me being stoopid from each rave to YouTube. Over time, these stories built up into a massive archive of the best moments of my life, traveling the country for the best times with some of the best people in one of my favorite cultures on the planet 🌎hope it provides some kind of entertainment or exposure to one of the most accepting cultures on the planet.

Here’s a small vid intro to my series with one of my favorite ncs songs from high school (full video and ig story highlights on youtube)

FOLLOW ME ON
Instagram: https://www.instagram.com/nylenayga
TikTok: @nylenayga
Facebook: https://www.facebook.com/nyle.nayga
Twitter: https://twitter.com/nylenayga
YouTube: https://www.youtube.com/nylenayga

node.text:
Tag a buddy who’s shoulders look more like prunes than grapes 🍇 

New Beyond EAA’s Grape flavor’s my new favorite, second only to pineapple. Reminds me of the good days throwing grapes at girls on the playground. My current supp stack is 1/2 scoop OxyShred, 1/2 scoop OxyShred Non-Stim, 1 scoop PSI, and 1 scoop EAA’s @ehplabs
🤘 Code ‘NYLE10’ for 10% discount and to support my videos bro🤘

High-Pump 3D Shoulder Workout:
1. Seated Bent-Over Dumbbell V-Raise - 4 x 15-16
2. My Front-Lateral-Rear Raise Combo - 4 x 24-27 total
 • Starts the pump off
3. Seated Bent-Over Mid/Rear Lateral Raise - 4 x 15-16
 • Should feel engagement in mid/rear delt 
4. Overhead Front Plate Raise w/ Alternating Partials - 4 x 16-18
5. Reverse Overhead Press Machine - 3 x 8-10, 2 x 15-16 per side
 • Sitting reverse may help more comfortable ROM depending on machine
6. Single-Arm Thumbs-Down Bent-Over Rear-Delt Raise - 5 x 18-20

Notes:
Start with Overhead Press Machine, rest in order. 2-3min rests between same exercises. One very light warm-up set each exercise before the sets above. Work up to heaviest weight by 2nd set. About (beginner: 2-4 reps/advanced: 1-2 reps) from failure each set. Final set of 3, 5, 6 to failure.
-
👕 Wearing @youngla • Use ‘NYLE’ for 15% OFF
-
💪 ***www.nylenayga.com*** (in my bio)
Visit to explore my 1-on-1 COACHING Services, Personalized Bodybuilding PROGRAMS, or become a personal client @naygagains 👈👈
-
📸: @rowenamcapo
-
🎵: Apashe - Good Times
-
❗️My workouts tend to be more volume than optimal for beginner lifters. I make these routines for the purpose of building aesthetics based on the knowledge I’ve gained over the years in what workout splits and exercises I used to build and shape my own body. Each workout is provided with the intention of being a new routine for you in case you’ve hit a pleateau in progress with your current routine. 
In the end, progressive overload is what will drive hypertrophy (muscle gain), and the best way to actively measure progressive overload “accurately” is to measure the total volume of work done on that muscle group(s) and increase that volume by a small increment at each proceeding recurrence of that muscle group

Smash or no smash?

Just uploaded my newest chest & tricep workout to the tooob. High-volume mass sender with tips, hacks and descriptions. Check it by clicking my story or the link in my bio 🎥

Tag a friend with invisible lat syndrome

Wearing new @youngla joggers: New drop today is LIVE (12pm pst)
👑Code ‘NYLE’ for 15% off👑

Back & Bi’s Workout:
1. Pendlay Row - 4 x 10-12
2. Overhand-to-Underhand Single-Arm Row - 4 x 8-10
 • Will add a little lat work in addition to mid back and rear delts
3. Palms-Down to Thumbs-Down Reverse Flys - 4 x 12-14
4. Medium-Grip Underhand Lat Pulldown - 4 x 10-12
5. Single-Arm Lat Pulldown Plate-Loaded Machine - 4 x 16-18 per side
 • Crunching/bending at the lat with each rep will further help engage the lat
6. Warm-Up: Wide-Grip Pull-Ups w/ mid-rep Pause - 3 x amrap

Biceps:
7. Hamburger🍔 Curl Dropset - 4 x 12-15
 • Drop weight twice per set and do amrap

Notes:
2-3min rests between same exercises. One very light warm-up set each exercise before the sets above. Work up to heaviest weight by 2nd set. About (beginner: 2-4 reps/advanced: 1-2 reps) from failure each set. Final set of 3, 5, 7 to failure.
-
🧬I take @ehplabs Pride, OxyShred Non-Stim, & PSI for pre-workout • Use ‘NYLE10’ for 10% OFF
-
💪 ***www.nylenayga.com*** (in my bio)
Visit to explore my 1-on-1 COACHING Services, Personalized Bodybuilding PROGRAMS, or become a personal client @naygagains 👈👈
-
📸: @rowenamcapo
-
❗️My workouts tend to be more volume than optimal for beginner lifters. I make these routines for the purpose of building aesthetics based on the knowledge I’ve gained over the years in what workout splits and exercises I used to build and shape my own body. Each workout is provided with the intention of being a new routine for you in case you’ve hit a pleateau in progress with your current routine. 
In the end, progressive overload is what will drive hypertrophy (muscle gain), and the best way to actively measure progressive overload “accurately” is to measure the total volume of work done on that muscle group(s) and increase that volume by a small increment at each proceeding recurrence of that muscle group throughout your program. 

The easiest way to ensure you’re increasing volume is by keeping the exercises of each recurrence of that muscle group a constant in order to eliminate exercise variance as a variable.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by IFBB PRO K-Pop Goku on September 03, 2021 tagging @ryanfreeman_93, and @dionterryfit. May be an image of 3 people and people standing.

node.text:
Happy Birthday Ryan

This year my biggest goal was to practice gratitude everyday, and even though you’ve physically left this world, you’re there for me every morning, reminding me how blessed I am to be alive and on this Earth - with the beautiful life and friends I have. You’re always reminding me to live. Just like when I’d be holed up in my room editing videos, you’d come in, say it’s break time m*therf*ker, and drag me out to a beach rave. Live everyday in pure joy like there’s no tomorrow 🕉

We just posted the video of your bonfire memorial up on my u2b channel. Hope you like it bro 🤙

Forever best friends and you’re still invited to be one of my best men at my wedding. Love you man.

To watch, click the link in my bio

node.text:
Tag a friend that needs bigger tits (. )( .)

Chest & Tri’s Workout:
1. Alternating Incline Dumbbell Press - 4 x 6-8
2. Weighted Dips - 4 x 8-10
 • Use legs to lean forward & focus lower chest
3. Weighted Close-Grip Push-Up on Bench - 4 x 16-18
 • Visualize pushing your hands together during each contraction to focus chest
4. Incline Dumbbell Fly - 4 x 12-14
5. Lower Chest Single-Arm Scoop Fly - 4 x 15-16
6. Finisher: Nyle Squeeze Press Pullover Dropset - 3 x 10/amrap (go to failure then dropset to lighter plate)
 • A finishing movement I improvised to focus upper chest + serratus w/ isometric + failure training

Tricep:
7. Supinated-Grip Overhead Tricep Extension - 5 x 15-16 (triple dropset last set)

Notes:
2-3min rests between same exercises. One very light warm-up set each exercise before the sets above. Work up to heaviest weight by 2nd set. About (beginner: 2-4 reps/advanced: 1-2 reps) from failure each set. Final set of 3, 5, 6, 7 to failure.
-
👕Wearing @youngla 
Code ‘NYLE’ for 15% off
-
🧬I take @ehplabs Pride, OxyShred Non-Stim, & PSI for pre-workout • Use ‘NYLE10’ for 10% OFF
-
💪 ***www.nylenayga.com*** (in my bio)
Visit to explore my 1-on-1 COACHING Services, Personalized Bodybuilding PROGRAMS, or become a personal client @naygagains 👈👈
-
📸: @trevinfit
-
🎵: Apashe - Dies Irae
-
❗️My workouts tend to be more volume than optimal for beginner lifters. I make these routines for the purpose of building aesthetics based on the knowledge I’ve gained over the years in what workout splits and exercises I used to build and shape my own body. Each workout is provided with the intention of being a new routine for you in case you’ve hit a pleateau in progress with your current routine. 
In the end, progressive overload is what will drive hypertrophy (muscle gain), and the best way to actively measure progressive overload “accurately” is to measure the total volume of work done on that muscle group(s) and increase that volume by a small increment at each proceeding recurrence of that muscle group throughout your program. 

The easiest way to ensure you’re increasing volume is by keeping the exercises of each recurrence of that muscle group a constant

node.text:
CRUSH YOUR WORKOUT🍉 Tag a friend who skips leg day

Here’s my hint for what I think @ehplabs’s new OxyShred mystery flavor is. This pre honestly tastes so dank, I faked this dry scoop to mix it with actual water and drink it like a puss🔥
💠 Use ‘NYLE10’ for 10% off 💠

LEG WORKOUT:
1. Landmine Reverse Lunge Knee Up’s - 4 x 10-12
2. Landmine Clean & Squat - 3 x 15-16
* One clean & squat is one rep
3. Heel-Elevated Close-Stance Pause-Rep Back Squat - 4 x 8-10
* Quad focused. Use knee sleeves for safety.
4. Slow-Eccentric Good-mornings - 4 x 10-12
5. Single-Leg Mermaid Hamstring Curls - 3 x 10-12, 3 x 16-18
6. Pause-Rep Calf Raise - 3 x 8-10, 3 x 16-18
* Hold each rep for 1-sec @ max contraction as hard as you can

Notes:
Start with Heel-Elevated Back Squat. 2-3min rests between same exercises. One very light warm-up set each exercise before the sets above. Work up to heaviest weight by 2nd set. About (beginner: 2-4 reps/advanced: 1-2 reps) from failure each set. Final set of 5 & 6 to failure.
-
👕Wearing @youngla • NEW DROP 8/24 @ 12pm pst
Code ‘NYLE’ for 15% off
-
💪 ***www.nylenayga.com*** (in my bio)
Visit to explore my 1-on-1 COACHING Services, Personalized Bodybuilding PROGRAMS, or become a personal client @naygagains 👈👈
-
📸: @trevinfit 
-
❗️My workouts tend to be more volume than optimal for beginner lifters. I make these routines for the purpose of building aesthetics based on the knowledge I’ve gained over the years in what workout splits and exercises I used to build and shape my own body. Each workout is provided with the intention of being a new routine for you in case you’ve hit a pleateau in progress with your current routine. 
In the end, progressive overload is what will drive hypertrophy (muscle gain), and the best way to actively measure progressive overload “accurately” is to measure the total volume of work done on that muscle group(s) and increase that volume by a small increment at each proceeding recurrence of that muscle group throughout your program.
